  "root_text": {
    "sn11.21:0.1": "Saṁyutta Nikāya 11.21 ",
    "sn11.21:0.2": "3. Tatiyavagga ",
    "sn11.21:0.3": "Chetvāsutta ",
    "sn11.21:1.1": "Sāvatthiyaṁ jetavane. ",
    "sn11.21:1.2": "Atha kho sakko devānamindo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṁ abhivādetvā ekamantaṁ aṭṭhāsi. ",
    "sn11.21:1.3": "Ekamantaṁ ṭhito kho sakko devānamindo bhagavantaṁ gāthāya ajjhabhāsi: ",
    "sn11.21:2.1": "“Kiṁsu chetvā sukhaṁ seti, ",
    "sn11.21:2.2": "kiṁsu chetvā na socati; ",
    "sn11.21:2.3": "Kissassu ekadhammassa, ",
    "sn11.21:2.4": "vadhaṁ rocesi gotamā”ti. ",
    "sn11.21:3.1": "“Kodhaṁ chetvā sukhaṁ seti, ",
    "sn11.21:3.2": "kodhaṁ chetvā na socati; ",
    "sn11.21:3.3": "Kodhassa visamūlassa, ",
    "sn11.21:3.4": "madhuraggassa vāsava; ",
    "sn11.21:3.5": "Vadhaṁ ariyā pasaṁsanti, ",
    "sn11.21:3.6": "tañhi chetvā na socatī”ti. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "sn11.21:0.1": "Linked Discourses 11.21 ",
    "sn11.21:0.2": "Chapter Three ",
    "sn11.21:0.3": "Slain ",
    "sn11.21:1.1": "Near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove. ",
    "sn11.21:1.2": "And then Sakka, lord of gods, went up to the Buddha, bowed, stood to one side, ",
    "sn11.21:1.3": "and addressed him in verse: ",
    "sn11.21:2.1": "“When what is slain do you sleep at ease? ",
    "sn11.21:2.2": "When what is slain is there no sorrow? ",
    "sn11.21:2.3": "What is the one thing ",
    "sn11.21:2.4": "whose killing you approve?” ",
    "sn11.21:3.1": "“When anger’s slain you sleep at ease. ",
    "sn11.21:3.2": "When anger’s slain there is no sorrow. ",
    "sn11.21:3.3": "Anger has a poisonous root, ",
    "sn11.21:3.4": "and a honey tip, O Vāsava. ",
    "sn11.21:3.5": "The noble ones praise its killing, ",
    "sn11.21:3.6": "for when it’s slain there is no sorrow.” "
  },
